            "content": "Recommended Schedule: Camera inspect your sewer line every 3-5 years if you have clay or cast iron pipes over 40 years old, every 5-7 years for homes with mature trees near sewer lateral, every 8-10 years for modern PVC systems in newer homes, and immediately after purchasing a pre-1980 home (or request inspection during escrow period). What It Catches: Progressive root intrusion before complete blockage occurs, developing cracks that can be sealed before they worsen, joint separations in early stages, early-stage corrosion in cast iron pipes, grade problems causing slow drainage, and deteriorating pipe sections before collapse. Cost vs. Value: $350-$450 for camera inspection vs. $8,000-$18,000 for emergency sewer replacement after catastrophic failure. Early detection typically reduces repair costs by 60-70% compared to emergency repairs. We include camera inspection with all [link:/services/plumbing-maintenance|plumbing maintenance plans], making this critical preventive measure affordable and convenient."
